SIMPLE: easy-going
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: easy-going
<hw>eas"y-go`ing</hw></mhw>
<pr>(⟦emac⟧z"⟦ycr⟧*g⟦omac⟧`⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Moving easily; hence, mild-tempered; relaxed and casual;
ease-loving; inactive. Contrasted with <ant>tense</ant>.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> degage, easy-going, laid-back.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>having a lax moral or disciplinary standard.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns> <ant>strict</ant>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lenient.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>unhurried; <as>as, an <ex>easygoing</ex> pace</as>.
Opposite of <ant>hurried</ant>.</def> <wns>[wns=3]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> easy, leisurely.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>unaggressive; <as>as, his <ex>easygoing</ex>
approach to business</as>. Opposite of <ant>aggressive</ant>.</def>
<wns>[wns=4]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> low-pressure.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>easygoingness</ent>⟦br⟧
